PC Gamer, Eurogamer, Polygon, The Guardian)\n În mod surprinzător, industria de jocuri nu e mulțumită de includerea dependenței de jocuri în rândul bolilor recunoscute de OMS. (Variety, GamesIndustry.biz)\n Epic Games anunță premiile Unreal E3 Awards 2019. (Shacknews)\n Sistemul de inteligență artificială de la Google, DeepMind, a început să bată și jucătorii de Quake III. (Kotaku, Gamasutra)\n  Articole (critică, dev, design)  From Bubsy to System Shock, how indie devs bring old videogames back to life (PC Gamer) In praise of ultra-short games (Ars Technica) Augmented reality changes how people interact and communicate, study finds (Ars Technica) I may have found the cure for spoilers (Destructoid) Opinion: Accessibility Is Becoming The New Standard (Games Informer) Gaming for Good (Gamereactor) Can stories be apolitical? We asked some video game writers and narrative designers (VG247)  Actualitate  Pokémon is a masterclass in brand management (GamesIndustry.biz) Call of Duty games may need to stop pretending they can be ‘complex’ (Polygon) Time to take responsibility over gaming disorder (GamesIndustry.biz) Play fights: the joys and the dangers of video games (New Statesman)  Computex  OPINION: Will Navi Be Enough? (GameSpace) The 10 coolest, and downright weirdest things we saw at Computex 2019 (PC Gamer) The Coolest Stuff We Saw at Computex 2019 (Tom\u0026rsquo;s Hardware)  Not-a-review  Despite losing the spotlight to Fortnite, PUBG is still thriving in 2019 (PC Gamer) The strange and surreal Kids is part game, part short film (The Verge) Two Years Later, Night in the Woods is Still Relatable (Sidequest) Life After an El Presidente (First Person Scholar) The Friends of Ringo Ishikawa (DEEP HELL) Is Assassin\u0026#8217;s Creed Unity a better game now Notre-Dame is in ruins? (RPS) Outer Wilds and Inner Depth: Making Something New Out of the Old (Paste) Is Pathologic 2 Too Hard For Its Own Good? (Paste)  Industrie  Without loot boxes, what does the future of mobile gaming look like? (Destructoid) Casual Connect: \u0026lsquo;It was considered the most cardinal sin to make a sequel,\u0026rsquo; says Molyneux (GameDaily.biz) An Interview With Blizzard President J. Allen Brack (Games Informer) How everything has fallen into place for Tetris (GamesIndustry.biz) Sony: Next PlayStation\u0026rsquo;s success will depend on backwards compatibility and streaming (GamesIndustry.biz) In Theory: Could the Sony/Microsoft cloud partnership end the console war? (Eurogamer) How Superhot sold over two million copies and where its developer goes from here (PCGamesInsider.biz) Casual Connect: Indie development is \u0026lsquo;stagnant\u0026rsquo; says Braid creator, Jonathan Blow (GameDaily.biz)  Istorie, retrospectivă  Total War: Shogun 2 is still beautiful and ambitious in 2019 (PC Gamer) 40 years on, celebrating the Mattel Intellivision (Eurogamer) Hunting down the true origins of the battle royale craze (Polygon) How Blizzard’s Canceled Adventure Game Shaped The Future Of Warcraft (Games Informer) The making of Counter-Strike: How a Half-Life mod went from hobby project to the big leagues (PCGamesInsider.biz) Returning To The World\u0026hellip; Of Warcraft (Games Informer) GameCube chainsaw, Sonic Screwdriver and other strange game controllers (VideoGamesChronicle) Bubsy History: The Story of the World’s Greatest Video Game Mascot (Tedium) The RetroBeat: Aladdin is a Genesis masterpiece (VentureBeat) The Fall of Rise of the Robots (Kotaku) History of Game Design: The Suprisingly Ancient Origins of Pinball (Rempton Games)  Dev, making of, mecanici  The Incredible Real-Life Story Behind The Friends of Ringo Ishikawa (Kotaku) A Plague Tale: Innocence - a fascinating game powered by stunning tech (Eurogamer) War Stories: How This War of Mine manipulates your emotions (Ars Technica) Video: Using empathy as a game mechanic in Unravel (Gamasutra)  Design, world-building, artă  The Japanese myths and woodblock art behind Sekiro’s creatures (RPS) Oh P